---
trigger: file_edit
glob: apps/client/src/shells/*/hooks/*.ts,apps/client/src/store/useGameStore.ts
---

VERIFY CLIENT FIELD READS AGAINST SERVER PROJECTIONS.

Cartridge SYNC projections in `apps/game-server/src/projections.ts` strip sensitive
fields by phase. Before writing client code that reads a cartridge field
(e.g. `prompt.stances`, `dilemma.decisions`, `voting.votes`), verify the field
exists in the projection for the relevant phase:

- CONFESSION: `confessions` STRIPPED during COLLECTING/VOTING; `votes` only during VOTING
- GUESS_WHO: `answers` STRIPPED during ANSWERING; `guesses` STRIPPED during GUESSING
- DILEMMA: `decisions` STRIPPED during COLLECTING; `submitted: Record<playerId, bool>` is the pre-REVEAL signal
- WOULD_YOU_RATHER: uses `choices`, NOT `stances`/`responses`
- HOT_TAKE / PLAYER_PICK / PREDICTION: use `stances` / `responses`

If you need a uniform "did this player act" signal across prompt/dilemma types,
prefer reading an existing `submitted`-style field OR propose a new
`participated: Record<playerId, boolean>` projection — DO NOT invent fields
like `submissions` that don't exist in any machine.

Grep `apps/game-server/src/machines/cartridges/` for the machine shape, then
grep `apps/game-server/src/projections.ts` for the projection shape, BEFORE
proposing a client-side field read.
